headline.main: ADMIRAL BOEHM ALIVE, NAZI AGENCY ASSERTS; London Suicide Story Denied -- British Add Hess Data

lead_paragraph: Admiral Hermann Boehm, German Naval Commander in Chief in Norway, who was reported a suicide in dispatches from London on Saturday "is full of health at his post," according to a dispatch by the German Transocean Agency received here yesterday.
abstract: German news agency denies Boehm suicide; Brit radio names reptd aides to Hess
